<item>
            <title>[SPARK-3062] ShutdownHookManager is only available in Hadoop 2.x</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-3062</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;PR &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/1891&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;#1891&lt;/a&gt; leverages &lt;tt&gt;ShutdownHookManager&lt;/tt&gt; to avoid &lt;tt&gt;IOException&lt;/tt&gt; when &lt;tt&gt;EventLogging&lt;/tt&gt; is enabled. But unfortunately &lt;tt&gt;ShutdownHookManager&lt;/tt&gt; is only available in Hadoop 2.x. Compilation fails when building Spark with Hadoop 1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
